\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Final observability Gramian for the halo-L1 baseline. Left: the six eigenvalues span seven orders of magnitude (condition number $\approx 10^7$). Right: per-eigenvector weights show the two weakest modes are concentrated in the $\{x,y,v_x,v_y\}$ subspace and on $v_z$ respectively, consistent with the planar geometry of the L1 halo.}}{8}{figure.caption.12}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:obs}{{6}{8}{Final observability Gramian for the halo-L1 baseline. Left: the six eigenvalues span seven orders of magnitude (condition number $\approx 10^7$). Right: per-eigenvector weights show the two weakest modes are concentrated in the $\{x,y,v_x,v_y\}$ subspace and on $v_z$ respectively, consistent with the planar geometry of the L1 halo}{figure.caption.12}{}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {section}{\numberline {8}Reproducibility (item 9)}{8}{section.8}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Navigation-error to burn-error coupling map at the halo-L1 baseline. A fixed launch dispersion ($\sigma _{r,inj}=10^{-4}$) sets the truth trajectory; navigation error magnitude $\sigma _{r,est}$ is then swept on the horizontal axis. Both terminal miss and $\Delta v$ inflation grow super-linearly with $\sigma _{r,est}$ on a log-log scale, showing that the coupling is multiplicative rather than additive.}}{9}{figure.caption.13}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:coup}{{7}{9}{Navigation-error to burn-error coupling map at the halo-L1 baseline. A fixed launch dispersion ($\sigma _{r,inj}=10^{-4}$) sets the truth trajectory; navigation error magnitude $\sigma _{r,est}$ is then swept on the horizontal axis. Both terminal miss and $\Delta v$ inflation grow super-linearly with $\sigma _{r,est}$ on a log-log scale, showing that the coupling is multiplicative rather than additive}{figure.caption.13}{}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {section}{\numberline {9}Reproducing this report's figures}{9}{section.9}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Monte Carlo metric distributions on the halo-L1 baseline (16 trials in this run; $n=200$ recommended for a paper). Mean and median overlays match within numerical noise on every metric, indicating no heavy-tailed contamination at the configuration tested. NIS mean is centred near $2.0$ (target for 2-D bearing residuals) and NEES near $6.0$ (target for 6-D state). The $\Delta v$ inflation distribution is positive-tailed, consistent with bearing-only filters over-burning when they receive a noisier-than-expected residual.}}{10}{figure.caption.15}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:mc-hists}{{8}{10}{Monte Carlo metric distributions on the halo-L1 baseline (16 trials in this run; $n=200$ recommended for a paper). Mean and median overlays match within numerical noise on every metric, indicating no heavy-tailed contamination at the configuration tested. NIS mean is centred near $2.0$ (target for 2-D bearing residuals) and NEES near $6.0$ (target for 6-D state). The $\Delta v$ inflation distribution is positive-tailed, consistent with bearing-only filters over-burning when they receive a noisier-than-expected residual}{figure.caption.15}{}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {section}{\numberline {10}What was deferred and why}{10}{section.10}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Ablation by combo $(\textrm  {pointing} \times q_\textrm  {acc} \times \sigma _{px})$, $4$ trials per combo at the smoke-test scale. Top-left ($\log _{10}$): the nine fixed-pointing combos (Moon out of FOV) collapse to a single box because the filter never receives an update; this is a real signal that the framework correctly identifies, not a symptom. Top-right: $\Delta v$ inflation widens substantially at higher $\sigma _{px}$. Bottom: NEES drift and valid-rate trade-off across the estimator-tracking combos.}}{11}{figure.caption.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:abl-box}{{9}{11}{Ablation by combo $(\textrm {pointing} \times q_\textrm {acc} \times \sigma _{px})$, $4$ trials per combo at the smoke-test scale. Top-left ($\log _{10}$): the nine fixed-pointing combos (Moon out of FOV) collapse to a single box because the filter never receives an update; this is a real signal that the framework correctly identifies, not a symptom. Top-right: $\Delta v$ inflation widens substantially at higher $\sigma _{px}$. Bottom: NEES drift and valid-rate trade-off across the estimator-tracking combos}{figure.caption.16}{}}
